Right, so the rain has gotten a little heavy and the players are walking off. A wise decision, considering the safety of the players. A good 40-45 minutes until we start losing overs but that isn't something we are worried about at the moment. 

 

16:36 Local Time, 03:36 GMT, 09:06 IST: We have started to lose overs now and there is no signs of the rain easing too.  The groundstaff are continously working to limit the damage on the square, but they need the overhead conditions to improve to get things moving. Some of the local fans have started to leave the stadium and that is never a good sign with considerable amount of time left in the game.

 

17:13 Local Time, 04:13 GMT, 09:43 IST: Some good news, the umbrellas are gone and the rain has stopped. If it stays this way, expect the match to in another 30-45 mins approx. How many overs will be lost, we will have to wait and watch. The latest possible start time is 8:04 pm local time. 

 

17:40 Local Time, 04:40 GMT, 10:10 IST: Just as the covers were being removed, a mild drizzle has started again and the covers are back on now. This pitch inspection will surely be delayed now. Seems like a passing cloud. Let's hope this doesn't last long. 

 

18:29 Local Time, 05:29 GMT, 10:59 IST: We have an update now for you. The play will begin at 18:40 local time and we will have a 29 overs match per side.

 

Revised playing conditions: Four bowlers can bowl a maximum of 6 overs and one bowler can bowl 5 overs.

19:21 Local Time, 06:21 GMT, 11:51 IST: AH, here it comes again. The umbrellas are out, the most used equipmet today. Just when the entertainment was starting in the form of Surya cutting loose, the rain gods have interruptted. Let's hope this is just a minor delay.

 

20:03 Local Time, 07:03 GMT, 12:33 IST: Okay, we have some bad news. The match has been called off, rain has the final say. The two umpires shake hands with the India captain, Shikhar Dhawan, and then with Kane Williamson. Both teams see the funny side of it and look all cheery while greeting each other.
